'''Ikee''' was a [[Computer worm|worm]] that spread by means of SSH Connections between [[iOS jailbreaking|jailbroken]] iPhones and stole [[Apple Inc|Apple]] ID's and passwords.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://nakedsecurity.sophos.com/2014/08/11/android-heart-app-virus-spreads-quickly-author-arrested-within-17-hours/ |title= First worm for IOS|accessdate=2014-08-11}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= https://gigaom.com/2009/11/12/ikee-iphone-worm-progeny-not-so-harmless/ |title= ikee iPhone Worm - Not So Harmless|accessdate=2009-11-12}}</ref> It was discovered in 2009 and changed wallpapers to a photo of [[Rick Astley]].<ref>{{cite web|url= http://news.softpedia.com/news/A-Safe-Mobile-Device-Starts-with-Its-Owner-475184.shtml|title= Ikee iPhone virus of 2009|accessdate=2015-03-08}}</ref>
==History== iPhone owners of [[Australia]] reported that smart phones had been infected by a worm that changed their iPhone wallpaper to Rick Astley, a 1980s pop singer.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.zdnet.com/article/source-code-for-ikee-iphone-worm-in-the-wild/|title= Ikee worm targeting customers of Australian mobile carriers|accessdate=2009-11-10}}</ref> It affected smartphones if the owner did not change their default password after installation of SSH. Once the Ikee worm infected, it would find other iPhones on the [[Cellular network|mobile network]] which were vulnerable and infect them as well. The worm wouldn’t affect users who hadn't jailbroken or installed SSH on their iPhone.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://nakedsecurity.sophos.com/2009/11/08/iphone-worm-discovered-wallpaper-rick-astley-photo/|title= First iPhone worm discovered – ikee |accessdate=2009-11-08}}</ref> The worm does nothing more than changing the infected user’s lock [[Wallpaper (computing)|screen wallpaper]].<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.computerweekly.com/news/1280091290/First-ever-iPhone-worm-Ikee-unleashed-by-Aussie-hacker|title= First ever iPhone worm Ikee unleashed by Aussie hacker|accessdate=2009-11-09}}</ref> The [[source code]] of the ikee worm says it was written by Ikex.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.sophos.com/en-us/press-office/press-releases/2009/11/iphone-worm-job.aspx|title= Ikee worm author wins job at iPhone app firm|accessdate=2009-11-26}}</ref>
